-----BEGIN PRIVATE KEY-----
THIS IS A PLACEHOLDER — NOT A REAL KEY. DO NOT USE.

Generate your own local-development key pair (never commit the result):

    openssl genrsa -out tmobile_private.pem 2048
    openssl rsa -in tmobile_private.pem -pubout -out tmobile_public.pem

Then point the app at it for LOCAL DEV ONLY via api/.env:

    TMOBILE_PRIVATE_KEY_PATH=./tmobile_private.pem

In production (Render / Docker / CI) DO NOT use a file. Provide the PEM
content directly via the environment variable instead:

    TMOBILE_PRIVATE_KEY_PEM="-----BEGIN PRIVATE KEY-----\n...\n-----END PRIVATE KEY-----"

The loader (api/app/integrations/tmobile_taap.py :: _load_private_key) prefers
TMOBILE_PRIVATE_KEY_PEM over TMOBILE_PRIVATE_KEY_PATH and converts escaped "\n"
sequences to real newlines, so a single-line env var works.

Real *.pem / *.key files are git-ignored (see .gitignore). Send the PUBLIC key
(tmobile_public.pem) to your T-Mobile account manager; keep the PRIVATE key out
of the repo entirely.
-----END PRIVATE KEY-----
